		<body>
				<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>New York</placeName> <date>12<hi rend="sup">th</hi> November 1850</date></p>
				<p><addressee>Revd. Isaac Leeser</addressee></p>
			<p rend="indent(1)"><placeName>Philadelphia</placeName></p>
			<p rend="indent(2)">Dear Sir</p>
			<p rend="indent(3)">I will feel particularly obliged by<lb/> you letting me know by the Earliest mail the price of a<lb/> full set of Hebrew prayer Books.  I want the Parasa<add>&#63;</add> Books also<lb/> I believe they are 10 Books in all&#44; say all the St<add>&#63;</add> days including<lb/> <date>Kepur<add>&#63;</add></date> prayers&#8212;I dont wish them extravagantly bound&#44; those bound<lb/> in plain board will annew&#44; but it should be as well to say<lb/> the price for them as well as those full Bound with my name<lb/> on the cover in gold letters&#44; as you may be able to get them<lb/> cheaper Bound than I am.  Trusting you are well.</p>
			<p rend="indent(4)">I am my Dear Sir</p>
			<p rend="indent(5)">Yours Respectfully</p>
			<p rend="indent(5)"><persName role="author">D. Carvalho</persName></p>
				<p>Please direct</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">to the <placeName>Irving Hotel</placeName></p>
			<p rend="indent(2)"><placeName>No 7 Greenwich Street</placeName></p>
			<p rend="indent(3)"><placeName>NYork</placeName></p>
		</body>
